# Paths excluded from ASH (Automated Security Helper) scans.
# ASH discovers this file via get_scan_set.py and applies it as a pathspec
# before any scanner runs, so excluded paths never reach individual scanners.
#
# Syntax is gitignore-style, using **/dirname/** form to unambiguously match
# files inside the directory at any depth.
#
# NOTE: igittigitt's IgnoreParser is invoked by ASH's get_scan_set.py with
# base_path="/", which anchors non-** patterns to the filesystem root. Patterns
# without a leading **/ therefore only match /dirname/... (literal root) and
# never match the actual repo path. Always prefix directory exclusions with
# **/ unless you really mean "from repo root on disk".

# Dependencies
**/node_modules/**

# Build output
**/dist/**
**/build/**

# CDK
**/cdk.out/**

# Test / coverage caches
**/coverage/**

# TypeScript build info
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# ASH internal outputs and logs (scanning our own scan artifacts is noise)
.ash/ash_output/**
.ash/analyze_out.txt
.ash/scan_out.txt
.ash/validate_out.txt
